’ђђЩТTitle: Datetime
Path: Additional language notes
Content:
Dates and times are held together in the 
``datetime``
 type. Date values used by the system are timezone-aware. By default, dates use the UTC timezone.
—Щharchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/lang-guide/chapters/types/basic_types/datetime.mdЩ@d7184211573c909236b6b8a1e7a4325e2ba5be14f686af57b9ebeb646c036ce7ЁDatetime‘Щ&Common commands that can be used with ЩЩ``datetime``
Many of Nushell's builtin commands are datetime aware and output or use 
``datetime``
 values

for fields and expressions. For example:
``date``
 and its subcommands
``format date``
``ls``
``ps``
``sys``
’ђђЪTitle: Datetime
Path: Common commands that can be used with 
Content:
``datetime``
Many of Nushell's builtin commands are datetime aware and output or use 
``datetime``
 values

for fields and expressions. For example:
``date``
 and its subcommands
``format date``
``ls``
``ps``
``sys``
